text: Neumarkt-Sankt Veit (until 1934 the town was called Neumarkt an der Rott) is a town in Mühldorf, in Bavaria, Germany. It is on the river Rott, 10 kilometers north of Mühldorf, and 33 kilometers southeast of Landshut. ==Twin towns and cities== Neumarkt-Sankt Veit is twinned with: * Caneva, Italy, since 2002 ==References== ==Other websites== * *Verwaltungsgemeinschaft Neumarkt-Sankt Veit Category:Mühldorf (district)
title: Neumarkt-Sankt Veit
